The Telegraph - Calcutta : International

 Tuesday, February 08, 2005 

 Cuba ban

 Havana, Feb. 7 (Reuters): Cuba, which evokes images of cigar-chomping revolutionaries, banned smoking in public places today, an uphill struggle in a country synonymous with fine tobacco.

 Cubans are no longer allowed to smoke in air-conditioned areas, offices, schools and sports centres in an island-wide health drive by President Fidel Castro?s government.




